messages.message:
I also tested out the new ‘Complex Prompts’ on UAT today, these are giving much better results now its using the same approach as converse. However we seem to have a regression is the UI in a few places.

https://www.loom.com/share/69b808f746f64b64b8633ad0d8e8ccc7

1. The loading spinner when you submit a prompt isn’t inside the input box correctly. 
2. You can see an error in the field name input before AI renames your field (if it is able to)
3. The renaming sometimes doesn’t work. 
Are these issues known?
by 3, do you mean that after the prompt is processed, the new field name could still be invalid?
Hey @CJ yep thats it, i’ve noticed the platform tries to rename without invalid characters, sometimes this fails. I think this shown at the end of the video.
